# Project Rules — GenWS (Expo React Native)

## Tech Stack
- Framework: Expo SDK 54 with Expo Router v4
- Language: TypeScript (strict mode)
- Styling: NativeWind v4 (Tailwind CSS for React Native)
- Backend: Supabase (Auth, Database, Storage, Edge Functions, Realtime)
- State: Zustand for global state
- Navigation: Expo Router (file-based routing)
- Notifications: expo-notifications + Expo Push API

## CRITICAL RULES
- NEVER use HTML elements (div, span, p, a, img, input, button)
- ALWAYS use React Native elements (View, Text, Image, TextInput, Pressable)
- NEVER use onClick — ALWAYS use onPress
- NEVER use className with web CSS — ONLY NativeWind classes
- NEVER use localStorage — use SecureStore or AsyncStorage
- ALWAYS use SafeAreaView for screen-level components
- ALWAYS handle both iOS and Android
- ALWAYS use functional components with TypeScript
- ALWAYS handle loading, error, and empty states
- All Supabase calls go through /lib/supabase.ts
- Type everything — no `any`

## File Naming
- Components: PascalCase (Button.tsx)
- Hooks: camelCase with "use" prefix (useAuth.ts)
- Routes: kebab-case in app/ directory

## Styling
- Use NativeWind className for ALL styling
- FlatList for lists (never map inside ScrollView)
- KeyboardAvoidingView for all form screens